    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-10T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–1147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-11T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 11, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 11—7:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2060. Following for President Truman from Representatives Cole,<note n="64"
                        xml:id="d692fn1">W. Sterling Cole (Republican), New York.</note>
                        Hébert,<note n="65" xml:id="d692fn2">F. Edward Hébert (Democrat),
                        Louisiana.</note> Hess<note n="66" xml:id="d692fn3">William E. Hess
                        (Republican), Ohio.</note> and Norblad,<note n="67" xml:id="d692fn4">Walter
                        Norblad (Republican), Oregon.</note> Members Armed Services Committee, House
                    of Representatives.</p>
                <p>A considered survey of Chinese-American interests prompts us to urge extension of
                    immediate aid to the Chinese Government by meeting its appropriate needs from
                    our available military materials and reviving implementation of previous
                    commitments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
